$$2$$ beds and $$4$$ chairs have a total mass of $$240$$$$\text{kg}$$. $$1$$ bed weighs as much as $$6$$ chairs. Find the mass of $$1$$ chair.
(A) 12$$ $$\text{kg}
(B) 15$$ $$\text{kg}
(C) 24$$ $$\text{kg}
(D) 30$$ $$\text{kg}

Points $(\sqrt{\pi}, a)$ and $(\sqrt{\pi}, b)$ are distinct points on the graph of $y^{2}+x^{4}=2 x^{2} y+1$. What is $\textbar a-b\textbar$?
(A) 1
(B) \frac{\pi}{2}
(C) 2
(D) \sqrt{1+\pi}
(E) 1+\sqrt{\pi}

For real numbers $w$ and $z$, $$ \frac{\frac{1}{w}+\frac{1}{z}}{\frac{1}{w}-\frac{1}{z}}=2014 $$ What is $\frac{w+z}{w-z} ?$
(A) - 2014
(B) \frac{-1}{2014}
(C) \frac{1}{2014}
(D) 1
(E) 2014

What is the solution of this equation: $$2^{2007}=4^{1003}\cdot x$$?
(A) 1
(B) 2
(C) \frac{1}{2}
(D) 2^{2}
(E) 2^{2008}

Two plums and one cherry weigh $$80\text{g}$$. One cherry and one plum weigh $$50\text{g}$$. What is the weight of four plums?
(A) 30\text{g}
(B) 40\text{g}
(C) 50\text{g}
(D) 120\text{g}
(E) 160\text{g}

